g section, which has name as required and errorCss with a default value.\n\nThe noCache tag is straightforward—it has no attributes at all, which matches the source exactly. The knowledge file correctly reflects this, and while the section is brief, that's just how it is.\n\nNow looking at codeSelect, which has quite a few attributes to verify. It inherits from GenericAttributesTag and requires both name and codeId, then has a range of standard form attributes like size, multiple, disabled, tabindex, and event handlers like onfocus, onblur, and onchange. There's also autofocus, pattern with a default of \"指定なし\", and opt.\n\nMoving into the optionColumnName section, I'm checking the attributes like labelPattern which defaults to $NAME$ and supports various placeholders including $SHORTNAME$, $OPTIONALNAME$ (which requires optionColumnName to be set), and $VALUE$. The listFormat defaults to br but can be div, span, ul, ol, or sp for space-separated values. There's also withNoneOption, noneOptionLabel which only applies when withNoneOption is true, errorCss defaulting to nablarch_error, and nameAlias for comma-separated values. The knowledge file has all of these covered.\n\nFor codeRadioButtons, the source shows it inherits from GenericAttributesTag with id not allowed, and FocusAttributesTag where accesskey isn't permitted.\n\nNow I'm verifying the fabrication check against the knowledge file. The typo \"windwo.open関数\" appears in both the source and knowledge file, so that's consistent. For allowDoubleSubmission, the source confirms the default is true.\n\nLooking at the section structure, the source has 15 complete tag sections plus the codeCheckboxesタグ anchor, and the knowledge file matches with 15 sections labeled s1-s15. Section s13 is intentionally brief since the source itself is short. Now checking the hints for completeness—I notice s1 (popupLinkタグ) is missing \"uri\" from its hints, even though uri is a required attribute. Looking through the remaining tag